import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Cases')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of wounds, other and disease cases over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['wounds'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Wounds Cases')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds cases?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    data['total'] = data['wounds'] + data['other'] + data['disease']
    data['wounds_prop'] = data['wounds'] / data['total']
    data['other_prop'] = data['other'] / data['total']
    data['disease_prop'] = data['disease'] / data['total']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['date'], data['wounds_prop'], label='Wounds', color='red')
    ax.bar(data['date'], data['other_prop'], bottom=data['wounds_prop'], label='Other', color='blue')
    ax.bar(data['date'], data['disease_prop'], bottom=data['wounds_prop'] + data['other_prop'], label='Disease', color='green')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Proportion')
    ax.set_title('What is the proportion of wounds cases compared to other and disease cases?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.date
    daily_cases = data.groupby('day').sum().mean(axis=1)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(daily_cases.index, daily_cases.values, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=daily_cases.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {daily_cases.mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Cases')
    ax.set_title('What is the average number of cases per day?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
